OL,3,CHeadteacher appears in court over
OL,4,Cschool assault
OL,6,FA solicitor representing Felton did
OL,7,Fnot apply for bail but said his
OL,8,Finstructions were that the defendant
OL,9,Fwas indicating a guilty plea to the
OL,10,Fcharge.
OL,12,FDistrict Judge Christopher James the
OL,13,Fdefendant in custody on remand saying,
OL,15,F"There are grounds to believe that if
OL,16,Freleased on bail there would be the
OL,17,Fcommission of further offences and
OL,18,Finterference with witnesses."
